#Text=San
#Text=Jose ( Occidental Mindoro )
#Text=San Jose
#Text=is a municipality in Occidental Mindoro , Philippines .
#Text=Understand
#Text=Even with its considerable tourism potential , San Jose has yet to turn into a more popular destination at par with other parts of the Philippines .
#Text=Among the challenges the town faces are coastal pollution , illegal settlers , and a lack of an effective ecotourism plan .
#Text=Brownouts caused by a lingering power supply dispute have negatively affected local businesses and tourism .
#Text=However , a modest number of visitors continue to explore this quaint town on the southwestern tip of Mindoro .
#Text=San Jose offers an off-the-beaten-path charm for local and foreign tourists alike who shun the crowded and over-commercialized spots in the country .
#Text=The major attractions of San Jose are its three offshore islands - Ambulong , Ilin , and White Island ( also called Manadi ) .
#Text=San Jose is also a favorite jump-off point to the world-class diving site - Apo Reef Marine Park .
#Text=By plane
#Text=San Jose Airport
#Text=( SJI formerly known as McGuire Field ) .
#Text=With regular scheduled flights to Manila by Cebu Pacific .
#Text=Flights take approximately 30 minutes from Manila .
#Text=By land
#Text=Dimple Star

#Text=, RORO Bus , and Philtranco has a direct bus route from Cubao in Quezon City , Sampaloc in Manila and Alabang in Muntinlupa ) to San Jose that includes a roll-on/roll-off ( RORO ) ferry that operates between Abra de Ilog and Batangas City which passes through Verde Island Passage which takes about three hours .
#Text=Only RORO Bus and Philtranco served this route as of 2018 , after Dimple Star 's operations were suspended after a deadly crash on the winding roads to this town .
#Text=San Jose is linked to all towns of Occidental Mindoro via a mostly-dusty provincial highway that runs from north to south .
#Text=Roads in and around San Jose are well-paved on mostly flat terrain .
#Text=Local bus and jeepney operators ply the route from the northernmost town of Abra de Ilog all the way south to San Jose .
#Text=Vans run from the bus terminal all the way to Calapan ( 6 hr , ₱500 ) along the eastern coast of Mindoro .
#Text=By sea
#Text=has boats to and from Coron three times a week ( ₱800 , 8 hr ) .
#Text=You can book tickets or find out about the schedule on biyaheroes.com .
#Text=Get around
#Text=Most roads in the Poblacion area and nearby barangays are either paved with concrete or asphalt .
#Text=The major thoroughfares are Rizal Street , Liboro Street , Bonifacio Street , Mabini Street , and the streets in and around the public market .
#Text=Motored tricycles are the common mode of transportation around town .
#Text=Jeepneys provide the main mode of public transportation between San Jose and other towns of the province .
#Text=Pump boats can be chartered to provide access to nearby island resorts and diving spots .
#Text=See
#Text=Ambulong Island
#Text=.
#Text=Ambulong Island is a 30-km² island with fine beaches , cliffs and abundant coral formations .
#Text=It is characterized by white sand beaches , cliffs along pillars jutting out of the water , and underwater caves .
#Text=Coral gardens and tropical fish are abundant in several coves .
#Text=An islet called Grace Island is located at a limestone cove at the southern tip of Ambulong .
#Text=A fisherman 's village is located at the sheltered side of the island .

#Text=Ambulong Island is also a jump-off point to some of the dive spots in the area , such as the Iling Point , Baniaga Reef , Ambulong Bank , Dungan Reef , Sardines Reef , Apo Reef , and Manadi Island .
#Text=These dive sites are about an hour away by pumpboat from the Caminawit Port .
#Text=Ilin Island
#Text=.
#Text=Ilin Island has a village of shell divers , being abundant in shells and coral reefs .
#Text=There are ancient burial caves of early Chinese traders , ethnic fishing villages , and numerous dive sites from which to view many tropical fishes .
#Text=Lush foliage encircle the clear blue waters of the South China Sea .
#Text=There are scuba diving facilities , a 6.8 CTM compressor , seaport facilities , diveboats , and PADI and NAUI-certified instructors .
#Text=Kweba Cansubong is a popular destination in the island apart from its white beaches , estuaries , rock formations , etc.
#Text=Inasakan Beach , located at the far side of Ilin , is a small stretch of powdery white sand .
#Text=Recently , the island 's timberland is being proposed to be declared a conservation area for its natural fauna and flora .
#Text=The Philippine teak , an endangered Philippine tree , is found only in Ilin and Batangas .
#Text=Meanwhile , an endangered fauna called the cloud rat ( or cloud runner/Ilin Island cloud runner ) is found only in San Jose , Occidental Mindoro particularly in the island of Ilin .
#Text=The cloud rat is the biggest and one of the most beautiful rats in the world .
#Text=White Island
#Text=( 15 minutes pumboat from Camanawit Port ) .
#Text=White Island has a long powdery beach where buried turtle eggs are occasionally found .
#Text=It has an almost mile-long beach with smooth and powdery white sand .
#Text=The tranquil and peaceful island is an ideal place for swimming , scuba diving and fishing .
#Text=Turtle eggs are occasionally found buried in the sand , and visitors are cautioned to keep them undisturbed .
#Text=Mt .
#Text=Iglit National Park
#Text=.
#Text=Mounts Iglit-Baco National Park is located in an area shared by the municipalities of Sablayan , Calintaan , Rizal and San Jose .
#Text=The latter is also the main gateway there .
#Text=It is a sanctuary for the ' tamaraw ' ( Bubalus mindorensis ) , an endemic species of buffalo found only in Mindoro .
#Text=It provides a nice eco-tourism , trekking , or mountaineering alternative to beach/dive resorts .

#Text=However , a part of the tamaraw genepool which is also a part of the national park is situated at the boundaries of Rizal and San Jose , more or less 50 hectares are in the territorial jurisdiction of the municipality .
#Text=Aroma Beach
#Text=, Bubog Rd. .
#Text=A favorite sport for local residents near San Jose Airport .
#Text=The beach is named after aroma trees in the area .
#Text=Second Landing Marker
#Text=, Bugbog Rd. .

#Text=World War II Marker commemorating the second landing of Gen. Douglas MacArthur in the Philippines in December 15 , 1944 which led to the Liberation of Manila and mainland Luzon from occupying Japanese forces .
#Text=The granite marker is complemented by three murals .
#Text=San Jose Municipal Plaza
#Text=, Rizal St. .
#Text=The town center and the destination , locals and tourist alike .
#Text=Also has a park .
#Text=Town festivities and events are also held in this area especially in the grandstand area .
#Text=A handful of souvenirs and merchandise can be bought here especially during the annual town fiesta in May or Christmas season .
